{
  "video_id": "8rZzHkpyPkc",
  "title": "For more wonder, rewild the world | George Monbiot",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12212.0,
      "end_time": 14285.0,
      "text": "When I was a young man, I spent six years"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14285.0,
      "end_time": 16398.0,
      "text": "of wild adventure in the tropics"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 16398.0,
      "end_time": 18526.0,
      "text": "working as an investigative journalist"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 18526.0,
      "end_time": 21911.0,
      "text": "in some of the most bewitching parts of the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 21911.0,
      "end_time": 25110.0,
      "text": "I was as reckless and foolish as only young men can be."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25110.0,
      "end_time": 26648.0,
      "text": "This is why wars get fought."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 26648.0,
      "end_time": 30875.0,
      "text": "But I also felt more alive than I&#39;ve ever done since."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 30875.0,
      "end_time": 34768.0,
      "text": "And when I came home, I found the scope of my existence"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 34768.0,
      "end_time": 36751.0,
      "text": "gradually diminishing"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 36751.0,
      "end_time": 41197.0,
      "text": "until loading the dishwasher seemed like an interesting challenge."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 41197.0,
      "end_time": 43337.0,
      "text": "And I found myself sort of"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 43337.0,
      "end_time": 45394.0,
      "text": "scratching at the walls of life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 45394.0,
      "end_time": 47432.0,
      "text": "as if I was trying to find a way out"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 47432.0,
      "end_time": 49319.0,
      "text": "into a wider space beyond."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 49319.0,
      "end_time": 53850.0,
      "text": "I was, I believe, ecologically bored."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 53850.0,
      "end_time": 58331.0,
      "text": "Now, we evolved in rather more challenging times than these,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 58331.0,
      "end_time": 63157.0,
      "text": "in a world of horns and tusks and fangs and claws."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 63157.0,
      "end_time": 65753.0,
      "text": "And we still possess the fear and the courage"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 65753.0,
      "end_time": 68946.0,
      "text": "and the aggression required to navigate those times."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 68946.0,
      "end_time": 73630.0,
      "text": "But in our comfortable, safe, crowded lands,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 73630.0,
      "end_time": 76613.0,
      "text": "we have few opportunities to exercise them"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 76613.0,
      "end_time": 79765.0,
      "text": "without harming other people."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 79765.0,
      "end_time": 83903.0,
      "text": "And this was the sort of constraint that I found myself"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 83903.0,
      "end_time": 86153.0,
      "text": "bumping up against."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 86153.0,
      "end_time": 88765.0,
      "text": "To conquer uncertainty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 88765.0,
      "end_time": 92083.0,
      "text": "to know what comes next,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 92083.0,
      "end_time": 96653.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s almost been the dominant aim of industrialized societies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 96653.0,
      "end_time": 100253.0,
      "text": "and having got there, or almost got there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 100253.0,
      "end_time": 103616.0,
      "text": "we have just encountered a new set of unmet needs."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 103616.0,
      "end_time": 106618.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve privileged safety over experience"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 106618.0,
      "end_time": 109122.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;ve gained a lot in doing so,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 109122.0,
      "end_time": 112130.0,
      "text": "but I think we&#39;ve lost something too."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 112130.0,
      "end_time": 114932.0,
      "text": "Now, I don&#39;t romanticize evolutionary time."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 114932.0,
      "end_time": 118450.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m already beyond the lifespan of most hunter-gatherers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 118450.0,
      "end_time": 121679.0,
      "text": "and the outcome of a mortal combat between me"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 121679.0,
      "end_time": 124592.0,
      "text": "myopically stumbling around with a stone-tipped spear"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 124592.0,
      "end_time": 127074.0,
      "text": "and an enraged giant aurochs"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 127074.0,
      "end_time": 129556.0,
      "text": "isn&#39;t very hard to predict."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 129556.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132552.0,
      "text": "Nor was it authenticity that I was looking for."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 132552.0,
      "end_time": 135692.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t find that a useful or even intelligible concept."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 135692.0,
      "end_time": 139618.0,
      "text": "I just wanted a richer and rawer life"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 139618.0,
      "end_time": 142114.0,
      "text": "than I&#39;ve been able to lead in Britain, or, indeed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 142114.0,
      "end_time": 145526.0,
      "text": "that we can lead in most parts of the industrialized world."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 145526.0,
      "end_time": 151032.0,
      "text": "And it was only when I stumbled across an unfamiliar word"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 151032.0,
      "end_time": 154637.0,
      "text": "that I began to understand what I was looking for."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 154637.0,
      "end_time": 157291.0,
      "text": "And as soon as I found that word,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 157291.0,
      "end_time": 159319.0,
      "text": "I realized that I wanted to devote"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 159319.0,
      "end_time": 163074.0,
      "text": "much of the rest of my life to it."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 163074.0,
      "end_time": 166575.0,
      "text": "The word is &quot;rewilding,&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 166575.0,
      "end_time": 169357.0,
      "text": "and even though rewilding is a young word,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 169357.0,
      "end_time": 171224.0,
      "text": "it already has several definitions."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 171224.0,
      "end_time": 175260.0,
      "text": "But there are two in particular that fascinate me."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 175260.0,
      "end_time": 179211.0,
      "text": "The first one is the mass restoration"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 179211.0,
      "end_time": 181866.0,
      "text": "of ecosystems."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 181866.0,
      "end_time": 184836.0,
      "text": "One of the most exciting scientific findings"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 184836.0,
      "end_time": 186606.0,
      "text": "of the past half century"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 186606.0,
      "end_time": 191352.0,
      "text": "has been the discovery of widespread trophic cascades."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 191352.0,
      "end_time": 194530.0,
      "text": "A trophic cascade is an ecological process"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 194530.0,
      "end_time": 196905.0,
      "text": "which starts at the top of the food chain"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 196905.0,
      "end_time": 200200.0,
      "text": "and tumbles all the way down to the bottom,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 200200.0,
      "end_time": 202543.0,
      "text": "and the classic example is what happened"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 202543.0,
      "end_time": 205354.0,
      "text": "in the Yellowstone National Park in the United States"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 205354.0,
      "end_time": 209443.0,
      "text": "when wolves were reintroduced in 1995."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 209443.0,
      "end_time": 213878.0,
      "text": "Now, we all know that wolves kill various species of animals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 213878.0,
      "end_time": 216277.0,
      "text": "but perhaps we&#39;re slightly less aware"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 216277.0,
      "end_time": 220115.0,
      "text": "that they give life to many others."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 220115.0,
      "end_time": 223228.0,
      "text": "It sounds strange, but just follow me for a while."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 223228.0,
      "end_time": 225054.0,
      "text": "Before the wolves turned up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 225054.0,
      "end_time": 226713.0,
      "text": "they&#39;d been absent for 70 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 226713.0,
      "end_time": 229778.0,
      "text": "The numbers of deer, because there was nothing to hunt them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 229778.0,
      "end_time": 232532.0,
      "text": "had built up and built up in the Yellowstone Park,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 232532.0,
      "end_time": 235623.0,
      "text": "and despite efforts by humans to control them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 235623.0,
      "end_time": 238318.0,
      "text": "they&#39;d managed to reduce much of the vegetation there"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 238318.0,
      "end_time": 241739.0,
      "text": "to almost nothing, they&#39;d just grazed it away."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 241739.0,
      "end_time": 243934.0,
      "text": "But as soon as the wolves arrived,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 243934.0,
      "end_time": 245761.0,
      "text": "even though they were few in number,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 245761.0,
      "end_time": 249660.0,
      "text": "they started to have the most remarkable effects."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 249660.0,
      "end_time": 251831.0,
      "text": "First, of course, they killed some of the deer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 251831.0,
      "end_time": 253643.0,
      "text": "but that wasn&#39;t the major thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 253643.0,
      "end_time": 255674.0,
      "text": "Much more significantly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 255674.0,
      "end_time": 258873.0,
      "text": "they radically changed the behavior of the deer."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 258873.0,
      "end_time": 261786.0,
      "text": "The deer started avoiding certain parts of the park,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 261786.0,
      "end_time": 264009.0,
      "text": "the places where they could be trapped most easily,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 264009.0,
      "end_time": 266748.0,
      "text": "particularly the valleys and the gorges,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 266748.0,
      "end_time": 269937.0,
      "text": "and immediately those places started to regenerate."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 269937.0,
      "end_time": 272336.0,
      "text": "In some areas, the height of the trees"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 272336.0,
      "end_time": 275348.0,
      "text": "quintupled in just six years."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 275348.0,
      "end_time": 279415.0,
      "text": "Bare valley sides quickly became forests of aspen"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 279415.0,
      "end_time": 281686.0,
      "text": "and willow and cottonwood."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 281686.0,
      "end_time": 283464.0,
      "text": "And as soon as that happened,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 283464.0,
      "end_time": 285622.0,
      "text": "the birds started moving in."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 285622.0,
      "end_time": 288043.0,
      "text": "The number of songbirds, of migratory birds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 288043.0,
      "end_time": 290117.0,
      "text": "started to increase greatly."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 290117.0,
      "end_time": 292174.0,
      "text": "The number of beavers started to increase,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 292174.0,
      "end_time": 294855.0,
      "text": "because beavers like to eat the trees."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 294855.0,
      "end_time": 298083.0,
      "text": "And beavers, like wolves, are ecosystem engineers."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 298083.0,
      "end_time": 300962.0,
      "text": "They create niches for other species."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 300962.0,
      "end_time": 303174.0,
      "text": "And the dams they built in the rivers"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 303174.0,
      "end_time": 306108.0,
      "text": "provided habitats for otters and muskrats"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 306108.0,
      "end_time": 310289.0,
      "text": "and ducks and fish and reptiles and amphibians."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 310289.0,
      "end_time": 314394.0,
      "text": "The wolves killed coyotes, and as a result of that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 314394.0,
      "end_time": 316856.0,
      "text": "the number of rabbits and mice began to rise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 316856.0,
      "end_time": 319766.0,
      "text": "which meant more hawks, more weasels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 319766.0,
      "end_time": 322165.0,
      "text": "more foxes, more badgers."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 322165.0,
      "end_time": 324652.0,
      "text": "Ravens and bald eagles came down to feed"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 324652.0,
      "end_time": 326888.0,
      "text": "on the carrion that the wolves had left."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 326888.0,
      "end_time": 330597.0,
      "text": "Bears fed on it too, and their population began to rise as well,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 330597.0,
      "end_time": 332940.0,
      "text": "partly also because there were more berries"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 332940.0,
      "end_time": 335252.0,
      "text": "growing on the regenerating shrubs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 335252.0,
      "end_time": 338483.0,
      "text": "and the bears reinforced the impact of the wolves"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 338483.0,
      "end_time": 342882.0,
      "text": "by killing some of the calves of the deer."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 342882.0,
      "end_time": 346558.0,
      "text": "But here&#39;s where it gets really interesting."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 346558.0,
      "end_time": 351843.0,
      "text": "The wolves changed the behavior of the rivers."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 351843.0,
      "end_time": 353530.0,
      "text": "They began to meander less."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 353530.0,
      "end_time": 357153.0,
      "text": "There was less erosion. The channels narrowed."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 357153.0,
      "end_time": 359548.0,
      "text": "More pools formed, more riffle sections,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 359548.0,
      "end_time": 361779.0,
      "text": "all of which were great for wildlife habitats."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 361779.0,
      "end_time": 363981.0,
      "text": "The rivers changed"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 363981.0,
      "end_time": 366193.0,
      "text": "in response to the wolves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 366193.0,
      "end_time": 369838.0,
      "text": "and the reason was that the regenerating forests"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 369838.0,
      "end_time": 373529.0,
      "text": "stabilized the banks so that they collapsed less often,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 373529.0,
      "end_time": 376849.0,
      "text": "so that the rivers became more fixed in their course."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 376849.0,
      "end_time": 380576.0,
      "text": "Similarly, by driving the deer out of some places"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 380576.0,
      "end_time": 384932.0,
      "text": "and the vegetation recovering on the valley sides,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 384932.0,
      "end_time": 386345.0,
      "text": "there was less soil erosion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 386345.0,
      "end_time": 389881.0,
      "text": "because the vegetation stabilized that as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 389881.0,
      "end_time": 393242.0,
      "text": "So the wolves, small in number,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 393242.0,
      "end_time": 396205.0,
      "text": "transformed not just the ecosystem"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 396205.0,
      "end_time": 399307.0,
      "text": "of the Yellowstone National Park, this huge area of land,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 399307.0,
      "end_time": 403525.0,
      "text": "but also its physical geography."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 403525.0,
      "end_time": 405149.0,
      "text": "Whales in the southern oceans"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 405149.0,
      "end_time": 407652.0,
      "text": "have similarly wide-ranging effects."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 407652.0,
      "end_time": 410519.0,
      "text": "One of the many post-rational excuses"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 410519.0,
      "end_time": 413509.0,
      "text": "made by the Japanese government for killing whales"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 413509.0,
      "end_time": 416643.0,
      "text": "is that they said, &quot;Well, the number of fish and krill will rise"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 416643.0,
      "end_time": 418881.0,
      "text": "and then there&#39;ll be more for people to eat.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 418881.0,
      "end_time": 420892.0,
      "text": "Well, it&#39;s a stupid excuse, but it sort of"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 420892.0,
      "end_time": 422261.0,
      "text": "kind of makes sense, doesn&#39;t it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 422261.0,
      "end_time": 424385.0,
      "text": "because you&#39;d think that whales eat huge amounts"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 424385.0,
      "end_time": 426547.0,
      "text": "of fish and krill, so obviously take the whales away,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 426547.0,
      "end_time": 428609.0,
      "text": "there&#39;ll be more fish and krill."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 428609.0,
      "end_time": 431002.0,
      "text": "But the opposite happened."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 431002.0,
      "end_time": 432331.0,
      "text": "You take the whales away,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 432331.0,
      "end_time": 435182.0,
      "text": "and the number of krill collapses."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 435182.0,
      "end_time": 437275.0,
      "text": "Why would that possibly have happened?"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 437275.0,
      "end_time": 440415.0,
      "text": "Well, it now turns out that the whales are crucial"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 440415.0,
      "end_time": 443728.0,
      "text": "to sustaining that entire ecosystem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 443728.0,
      "end_time": 445457.0,
      "text": "and one of the reasons for this"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 445457.0,
      "end_time": 447557.0,
      "text": "is that they often feed at depth"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 447557.0,
      "end_time": 449339.0,
      "text": "and then they come up to the surface and produce"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 449339.0,
      "end_time": 453525.0,
      "text": "what biologists politely call large fecal plumes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 453525.0,
      "end_time": 457958.0,
      "text": "huge explosions of poop right across the surface waters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 457958.0,
      "end_time": 461274.0,
      "text": "up in the photic zone, where there&#39;s enough light"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 461274.0,
      "end_time": 464446.0,
      "text": "to allow photosynthesis to take place,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 464446.0,
      "end_time": 467390.0,
      "text": "and those great plumes of fertilizer"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 467390.0,
      "end_time": 469382.0,
      "text": "stimulate the growth of phytoplankton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 469382.0,
      "end_time": 471296.0,
      "text": "the plant plankton at the bottom of the food chain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 471296.0,
      "end_time": 473394.0,
      "text": "which stimulate the growth of zooplankton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 473394.0,
      "end_time": 475691.0,
      "text": "which feed the fish and the krill and all the rest of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 475691.0,
      "end_time": 477825.0,
      "text": "The other thing that whales do is that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 477825.0,
      "end_time": 480554.0,
      "text": "as they&#39;re plunging up and down through the water column,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 480554.0,
      "end_time": 482922.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re kicking the phytoplankton"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 482922.0,
      "end_time": 484372.0,
      "text": "back up towards the surface"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 484372.0,
      "end_time": 487486.0,
      "text": "where it can continue to survive and reproduce."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 487486.0,
      "end_time": 490114.0,
      "text": "And interestingly, well, we know"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 490114.0,
      "end_time": 493051.0,
      "text": "that plant plankton in the oceans"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 493051.0,
      "end_time": 494858.0,
      "text": "absorb carbon from the atmosphere --"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 494858.0,
      "end_time": 496401.0,
      "text": "the more plant plankton there are,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 496401.0,
      "end_time": 498080.0,
      "text": "the more carbon they absorb --"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 498080.0,
      "end_time": 501162.0,
      "text": "and eventually they filter down into the abyss"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 501162.0,
      "end_time": 504542.0,
      "text": "and remove that carbon from the atmospheric system."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 504542.0,
      "end_time": 508843.0,
      "text": "Well, it seems that when whales were at their historic populations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 508843.0,
      "end_time": 511852.0,
      "text": "they were probably responsible for sequestering"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 511852.0,
      "end_time": 515645.0,
      "text": "some tens of millions of tons of carbon"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 515645.0,
      "end_time": 518334.0,
      "text": "every year from the atmosphere."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 518333.99999999994,
      "end_time": 521560.99999999994,
      "text": "And when you look at it like that, you think,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 521561.00000000006,
      "end_time": 523420.00000000006,
      "text": "wait a minute, here are the wolves"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 523419.99999999994,
      "end_time": 526437.0,
      "text": "changing the physical geography of the Yellowstone National Park."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 526437.0,
      "end_time": 528296.0,
      "text": "Here are the whales changing"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 528296.0,
      "end_time": 530936.0,
      "text": "the composition of the atmosphere."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 530936.0,
      "end_time": 533246.0,
      "text": "You begin to see that possibly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 533246.0,
      "end_time": 536927.0,
      "text": "the evidence supporting James Lovelock&#39;s Gaia hypothesis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 536927.0,
      "end_time": 539514.0,
      "text": "which conceives of the world as a coherent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 539514.0,
      "end_time": 541444.0,
      "text": "self-regulating organism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 541444.0,
      "end_time": 547178.0,
      "text": "is beginning, at the ecosystem level, to accumulate."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 547178.0,
      "end_time": 549446.0,
      "text": "Trophic cascades"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 549446.0,
      "end_time": 551507.0,
      "text": "tell us that the natural world"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 551507.0,
      "end_time": 556253.0,
      "text": "is even more fascinating and complex than we thought it was."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 556253.0,
      "end_time": 559985.0,
      "text": "They tell us that when you take away the large animals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 559985.0,
      "end_time": 563177.0,
      "text": "you are left with a radically different ecosystem"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 563177.0,
      "end_time": 566349.0,
      "text": "to one which retains its large animals."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 566349.0,
      "end_time": 569630.0,
      "text": "And they make, in my view, a powerful case"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 569630.0,
      "end_time": 573783.0,
      "text": "for the reintroduction of missing species."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 573783.0,
      "end_time": 575859.0,
      "text": "Rewilding, to me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 575859.0,
      "end_time": 579157.0,
      "text": "means bringing back some of the missing plants and animals."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 579157.0,
      "end_time": 580469.0,
      "text": "It means taking down the fences,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 580469.0,
      "end_time": 582493.0,
      "text": "it means blocking the drainage ditches,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 582493.0,
      "end_time": 585757.0,
      "text": "it means preventing commercial fishing in some large areas of sea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 585757.0,
      "end_time": 589171.0,
      "text": "but otherwise stepping back."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 589171.0,
      "end_time": 592981.0,
      "text": "It has no view as to what a right ecosystem"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 592981.0,
      "end_time": 595682.0,
      "text": "or a right assemblage of species looks like."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 595682.0,
      "end_time": 599461.0,
      "text": "It doesn&#39;t try to produce a heath or a meadow"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 599461.0,
      "end_time": 604147.0,
      "text": "or a rain forest or a kelp garden or a coral reef."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 604147.0,
      "end_time": 606164.0,
      "text": "It lets nature decide,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 606164.0,
      "end_time": 609983.0,
      "text": "and nature, by and large, is pretty good at deciding."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 609983.0,
      "end_time": 612258.0,
      "text": "Now, I mentioned that there are two definitions"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 612258.0,
      "end_time": 614104.0,
      "text": "of rewilding that interest me."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 614104.0,
      "end_time": 615361.0,
      "text": "The other one"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 615361.0,
      "end_time": 618384.0,
      "text": "is the rewilding of human life."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 618384.0,
      "end_time": 620447.0,
      "text": "And I don&#39;t see this as an alternative"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 620447.0,
      "end_time": 622371.0,
      "text": "to civilization."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 622371.0,
      "end_time": 625771.0,
      "text": "I believe we can enjoy the benefits of advanced technology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 625771.0,
      "end_time": 629610.0,
      "text": "as we&#39;re doing now, but at the same time, if we choose,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 629610.0,
      "end_time": 634626.0,
      "text": "have access to a richer and wilder life of adventure"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 634626.0,
      "end_time": 636209.0,
      "text": "when we want to because"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 636209.0,
      "end_time": 640605.0,
      "text": "there would be wonderful, rewilded habitats."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 640605.0,
      "end_time": 642389.0,
      "text": "And the opportunities for this"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 642389.0,
      "end_time": 647380.0,
      "text": "are developing more rapidly than you might think possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 647380.0,
      "end_time": 650359.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s one estimate which suggests that in the United States,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 650359.0,
      "end_time": 654044.0,
      "text": "two thirds of the land which was once forested and then cleared"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 654044.0,
      "end_time": 657547.0,
      "text": "has become reforested as loggers and farmers have retreated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 657547.0,
      "end_time": 660560.0,
      "text": "particularly from the eastern half of the country."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 660560.0,
      "end_time": 662217.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s another one which suggests"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 662217.0,
      "end_time": 665680.0,
      "text": "that 30 million hectares of land in Europe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 665680.0,
      "end_time": 668187.0,
      "text": "an area the size of Poland,"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 668187.0,
      "end_time": 670018.0,
      "text": "will be vacated by farmers"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 670018.0,
      "end_time": 673340.0,
      "text": "between 2000 and 2030."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 673340.0,
      "end_time": 676876.0,
      "text": "Now, faced with opportunities like that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 676876.0,
      "end_time": 679047.0,
      "text": "does it not seem a little unambitious"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 679047.0,
      "end_time": 682761.0,
      "text": "to be thinking only of bringing back wolves, lynx,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 682761.0,
      "end_time": 686360.0,
      "text": "bears, beavers, bison, boar, moose,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 686360.0,
      "end_time": 688185.0,
      "text": "and all the other species which are already beginning"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 688185.0,
      "end_time": 691449.0,
      "text": "to move quite rapidly across Europe?"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 691449.0,
      "end_time": 693973.0,
      "text": "Perhaps we should also start thinking"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 693973.0,
      "end_time": 697962.0,
      "text": "about the return of some of our lost megafauna."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 697962.0,
      "end_time": 699894.0,
      "text": "What megafauna, you say?"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 699894.0,
      "end_time": 702463.0,
      "text": "Well, every continent had one,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 702463.0,
      "end_time": 703944.0,
      "text": "apart from Antarctica."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 703944.0,
      "end_time": 707582.0,
      "text": "When Trafalgar Square in London was excavated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 707582.0,
      "end_time": 709337.0,
      "text": "the river gravels there were found"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 709337.0,
      "end_time": 712887.0,
      "text": "to be stuffed with the bones of hippopotamus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 712887.0,
      "end_time": 716975.0,
      "text": "rhinos, elephants, hyenas, lions."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 716975.0,
      "end_time": 718349.0,
      "text": "Yes, ladies and gentlemen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 718349.0,
      "end_time": 720545.0,
      "text": "there were lions in Trafalgar Square"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 720545.0,
      "end_time": 723751.0,
      "text": "long before Nelson&#39;s Column was built."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 723751.0,
      "end_time": 726002.0,
      "text": "All these species lived here"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 726002.0,
      "end_time": 728654.0,
      "text": "in the last interglacial period,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 728654.0,
      "end_time": 731515.0,
      "text": "when temperatures were pretty similar to our own."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 731515.0,
      "end_time": 733588.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not climate, largely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 733588.0,
      "end_time": 737135.0,
      "text": "which has got rid of the world&#39;s megafaunas."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 737135.0,
      "end_time": 739239.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s pressure from the human population"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 739239.0,
      "end_time": 741075.0,
      "text": "hunting and destroying their habitats"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 741075.0,
      "end_time": 743126.0,
      "text": "which has done so."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 743126.0,
      "end_time": 746914.0,
      "text": "And even so, you can still see the shadows"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 746914.0,
      "end_time": 749622.0,
      "text": "of these great beasts in our current ecosystems."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 749622.0,
      "end_time": 752575.0,
      "text": "Why is it that so many deciduous trees"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 752575.0,
      "end_time": 757133.0,
      "text": "are able to sprout from whatever point the trunk is broken?"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 757133.0,
      "end_time": 759202.0,
      "text": "Why is it that they can withstand the loss"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 759202.0,
      "end_time": 760809.0,
      "text": "of so much of their bark?"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 760809.0,
      "end_time": 763752.0,
      "text": "Why do understory trees,"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 763752.0,
      "end_time": 768845.0,
      "text": "which are subject to lower sheer forces from the wind"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 768845.0,
      "end_time": 770576.0,
      "text": "and have to carry less weight"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 770576.0,
      "end_time": 772978.0,
      "text": "than the big canopy trees,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 772978.0,
      "end_time": 776097.0,
      "text": "why are they so much tougher and harder to break"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 776097.0,
      "end_time": 780506.0,
      "text": "than the canopy trees are?"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 780506.0,
      "end_time": 782478.0,
      "text": "Elephants."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 782478.0,
      "end_time": 784647.0,
      "text": "They are elephant-adapted."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 784647.0,
      "end_time": 786935.0,
      "text": "In Europe, for example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 786935.0,
      "end_time": 790078.0,
      "text": "they evolved to resist the straight-tusked elephant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 790078.0,
      "end_time": 792366.0,
      "text": "elephas antiquus, which was a great beast."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 792366.0,
      "end_time": 794542.0,
      "text": "It was related to the Asian elephant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 794542.0,
      "end_time": 797111.0,
      "text": "but it was a temperate animal, a temperate forest creature."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 797111.0,
      "end_time": 799641.0,
      "text": "It was a lot bigger than the Asian elephant."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 799641.0,
      "end_time": 802458.0,
      "text": "But why is it that some of our common shrubs"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 802458.0,
      "end_time": 805642.0,
      "text": "have spines which seem to be over-engineered"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 805642.0,
      "end_time": 808305.0,
      "text": "to resist browsing by deer?"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 808305.0,
      "end_time": 810119.0,
      "text": "Perhaps because they evolved"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 810119.0,
      "end_time": 813382.0,
      "text": "to resist browsing by rhinoceros."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 813382.0,
      "end_time": 815306.0,
      "text": "Isn&#39;t it an amazing thought"
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 815306.0,
      "end_time": 818034.0,
      "text": "that every time you wander into a park"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 818034.0,
      "end_time": 820881.0,
      "text": "or down an avenue or through a leafy street,"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 820881.0,
      "end_time": 824492.0,
      "text": "you can see the shadows of these great beasts?"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 824492.0,
      "end_time": 828292.0,
      "text": "Paleoecology, the study of past ecosystems,"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 828292.0,
      "end_time": 832350.0,
      "text": "crucial to an understanding of our own,"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 832350.0,
      "end_time": 835927.0,
      "text": "feels like a portal through which you may pass"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 835927.0,
      "end_time": 838859.0,
      "text": "into an enchanted kingdom."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 838859.0,
      "end_time": 842672.0,
      "text": "And if we really are looking at areas of land"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 842672.0,
      "end_time": 846917.0,
      "text": "of the sort of sizes I&#39;ve been talking about becoming available,"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 846917.0,
      "end_time": 849632.0,
      "text": "why not reintroduce some of our lost megafauna,"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 849632.0,
      "end_time": 851582.0,
      "text": "or at least species closely related to those"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 851582.0,
      "end_time": 854543.0,
      "text": "which have become extinct everywhere?"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 854543.0,
      "end_time": 856852.0,
      "text": "Why shouldn&#39;t all of us"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 856852.0,
      "end_time": 859805.0,
      "text": "have a Serengeti on our doorsteps?"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 859805.0,
      "end_time": 862771.0,
      "text": "And perhaps this is the most important thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 862771.0,
      "end_time": 864246.0,
      "text": "that rewilding offers us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 864246.0,
      "end_time": 867840.0,
      "text": "the most important thing that&#39;s missing from our lives:"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 867840.0,
      "end_time": 869957.0,
      "text": "hope."
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 869957.0,
      "end_time": 874354.0,
      "text": "In motivating people to love and defend the natural world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 874354.0,
      "end_time": 879164.0,
      "text": "an ounce of hope is worth a ton of despair."
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 879164.0,
      "end_time": 881803.0,
      "text": "The story rewilding tells us"
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 881803.0,
      "end_time": 885443.0,
      "text": "is that ecological change need not always proceed"
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 885443.0,
      "end_time": 887906.0,
      "text": "in one direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 887906.0,
      "end_time": 890342.0,
      "text": "It offers us the hope"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 890342.0,
      "end_time": 892483.0,
      "text": "that our silent spring"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 892483.0,
      "end_time": 894814.0,
      "text": "could be replaced by a raucous summer."
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 894814.0,
      "end_time": 896034.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 896034.0,
      "end_time": 906034.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}